pull_request.title: Obfuscate legacy
pull_request.body:
### Overview

This PR adds other legacy code that was missed for obfuscation, that was noticed while fixing the test suite.

commits.message:
Obfuscate legacy (#221)

* split tests to run individually

* Trace IDs should be 32 bytes of random hex chars (#185)

* Trace IDs should be 32 bytes of random hex chars

The function as-is will always generate a trace ID that ends in 0. The reason is that the array passed to crypto.getRandomValues() only has 31 elements. That's fine when you're looking at the GUID function, which only has 31 random characters.

In the current code, the array is created with 31 elements, indexed 0-30. The last character is pulled using `randomVals[31]` which returns undefined, which gets translated to 0 (`undefined & 15 === 0`).

* Improve; generate only needed random bytes

* Db obfuscate (#191)

* split tests to run individually

* implement obfuscation

* cleanup

* Update obfuscation test to cover more failing cases

* Separate obfuscation from _send path

* fix tests and add supportability metric

* remove console log

* remove errant console.log, cleanup

* traverse and obfuscate any string

* fix test to run on supported browsers

* add validation for reserved characters

* cleanup

* Refactor obfuscation

* Add wip obfuscation unit test

* Add obfuscation unit tests, update obfuscation validation

* fix tests and add test for obfuscation supportability metrics

* update tests for compat

Co-authored-by: aubreymasten <aubreymasten@users.noreply.github.com>

* Make configuration of obfuscation more generic (#193)

* split tests to run individually

* implement obfuscation

* cleanup

* Update obfuscation test to cover more failing cases

* Separate obfuscation from _send path

* fix tests and add supportability metric

* remove console log

* remove errant console.log, cleanup

* traverse and obfuscate any string

* fix test to run on supported browsers

* add validation for reserved characters

* cleanup

* Refactor obfuscation

* Add wip obfuscation unit test

* Add obfuscation unit tests, update obfuscation validation

* fix tests and add test for obfuscation supportability metrics

* update tests for compat

* change obfuscateUrls to the more generic obfuscate

* obfuscate before serialization

* Remove missed merge conflict

Co-authored-by: aubreymasten <aubreymasten@users.noreply.github.com>

* obfuscate file protocol and add tests

* remove workflows

* clean up mock window and fix test

* remove obsolete test

* remove helper files from loader

* add supportability metric for file protocol detection

* update tests to better reflect encoding changes

* fix lint errors

Co-authored-by: jeffalder <49817386+jeffalder@users.noreply.github.com>
Co-authored-by: aubreymasten <aubreymasten@users.noreply.github.com>

issue.title: Nodes `fullHostname` appears as a service name if any service is bound to the host IP
issue.body:
## Description

If in the cluster there is a service having the host's IP address as an endpoint (e.g. a pod with `hostNetwork: true`), CoreDNS will return the service name as the reverse for the Host's IP, rather than forwarding this upstream.

This causes the agent to report that service name as the `fullHostname` for the node.

## Expected Behavior

`fullHostname` for the nodes should be the FQDN of the node, not a service name.
